## Door / Opening Direction

This scene is important for explicit opening-direction audit.

Verified hardware markers:

- `BG1` has `HINGES_BLUM#3` with dynamic name `Петля под фальшпанель Blum (С доводчиком)` on `FACADE1#4`.
- `PB2F` has hinge-related components on `FACADE1#9` / `FACADE2#3`, with `Петля внешняя Blum (С доводчиком)`.
- `TB2-H3` has hinge-related components on upper facades, with `Петля внешняя Blum (С доводчиком)`.
- `TB1#1` has hinge-related components on `FACADE1#7`, with `Петля внешняя Blum (С доводчиком)`.
- `BB1` has hinge-related components on `FACADE1#5`, with `Петля внешняя Blum (С доводчиком)`.

Functional interpretation:

- Drawer modules (`BD3#1`, drawer fronts) are pull-out/front-opening, not side-hinged doors.
- Dishwasher front (`BI#1`) opens downward/front; treat as appliance clearance, not a normal hinged cabinet door.
- `BG1` corner door is a hinged facade with false-panel hinge hardware; opening direction must be validated against corner access and adjacent row, not inferred from bbox only.
- `PB2F` integrated fridge pencil has two stacked front sections and real hinge hardware; generated scenes must preserve hinge side/opening clearance against the right end panel and wall.
- `TB2-H3` upper uses two facades in one wide upper module; do not collapse it into a single 876mm door without checking hardware/opening intent.

Template implication: opening direction must be audited from actual hardware/opening markers (`HINGES_BLUM`, `HINGE`, `HINGE_CUP`, `CUP_MARK`, `OPENING`, appliance type) and then cross-checked visually for wall/panel conflicts.

